    "description": "<p>We revolutionize Customer Service with Artificial Intelligence. Speed, passion and drive are the basis of our DNA. We put our customers at the center of everything we do, and we never stop until the job is done. We’re creating our own path, with a global and diverse team driving long-term growth and innovation. We don’t like “not possible”. We like new ideas, open-mindness, honesty and we always bring an element of fun into our work. Join our team and be ready to change the world with us.</p>\n<p>We are one of the leading companies in Artificial Intelligence, providing our services to the world's most innovative companies. With our expert team of application developers and data scientists we work closely together with our customers to always be ahead of the game and to create state-of-the-art technology. Become part of our fast-paced environment and join our team building the most innovative and revolutionary technology in the market.</p>\n<p>Some of our awards include: Insurance Disruptor of the Year, Impact Growth EU Tech of the Year, CCW Most Innovative CS Solution, Impact Diamond - Best InsurTech and many more.</p>\n<p>We recruit, employ, train, and promote regardless of race, religion, colour, national origin, sex, etc. We aim to be the place where a diverse mix of talented people want to come, to stay, and do their best work.</p>\n<p><strong>Tasks</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Define software architecture, components, infrastructure and non-functional product requirements</li>\n<li>Understand which solution best addresses customer’s needs and business requirements</li>\n<li>Identify and evaluate value-add alternatives for customers</li>\n<li>Provide solutions to meet client requirements and be able to adapt to new requirements</li>\n<li>Deliver against the defined business outcomes by using creative solutions to problems, and utilizing resources in an efficient way</li>\n<li>Provide solution advice, drive proposals, presentations, and other customer communications</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelor’s degree or foreign equivalent in Information Technology, Engineering, or equivalent</li>\n<li>Excellent written and oral communication skills in German and English</li>\n<li>Experience in project management</li>\n<li>Experience communicating complex technical concepts to external business and technical audience</li>\n<li>Development experience with at least one programming language</li>\n<li>Hands-on experience with Cloud Platforms (i.e. AWS, Azure, Google Cloud)</li>\n<li>Willingness to travel</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Benefits</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Office located in the heart of Munich, in Marienplatz</li>\n<li>A chance to meet people from all over the world! (20+ nationalities)</li>\n<li>We value learning. We support all job-related seminars or courses</li>\n<li>Free gym memberships</li>\n<li>Free German language courses</li>\n<li>Weekly yoga sessions in the office</li>\n<li>Regular company events such as Oktoberfest, Halloween, Christmas tree decoration</li>\n<li>A start-up atmosphere with table tennis, dart board, chill room</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>We are looking forward to hearing from you!</strong></p>\n<p>Best,</p>\n<p>e-bot7</p>\n",
